.SH DESCRIPTION
Replace the code point beginning at byte offset \f[CR]start_pos\f[R]
with \f[CR]c\f[R].
\f[CR]start_pos\f[R] cannot be less than 0.
If \f[CR]start_pos\f[R] is past the end of \f[CR]us\f[R] then the space
between the end of the string and \f[CR]start_pos\f[R] will be padded
with NUL (\f[CR]\[aq]\[rs]0\[aq]\f[R]) bytes.
If \f[CR]start_pos\f[R] is not the start of a valid code point, that is
an error and the string will be unmodified.
